cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 75 mi WNW of Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic
cyclone.trajectory: moving WNW across Hispaniola, forecast to skirt the Turks & Caicos and SE Bahamas, then track near/north of the north-coast of central Cuba, enter the Straits/SE Gulf on Saturday and turn northwest toward the FL Panhandle/AL coast by Monday
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Panhandle (near or east of Apalachicola, FL)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Dominican Republic south coast from Punta Palenque eastward, north coast east of Haiti–DR border; Haiti (northern coast) to Gonaives; Turks & Caicos; SE Bahamas; Cuban provinces from Guantánamo to Ciego de Ávila
weather_observation.warning_coast: Dominican Republic south coast from Punta Palenque eastward and north coast east of the Haiti–DR border
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Hispaniola, Turks & Caicos, SE & central Bahamas, north-central Cuba, Florida Keys, Florida Gulf Coast and eastern Gulf states
weather_observation.wind: Low chance (≤7% cumulative) of tropical-storm-force winds; breezy conditions possible late Sunday–Monday
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along NE Florida Atlantic coast from Fred
weather_observation.rainfall: 1–3 inches of intermittent heavy rain possible late weekend into Monday as outer bands sweep across NE Florida
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous rip currents along NE Florida Atlantic beaches beginning this weekend
